<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAR 94 / Health chairman is sacked
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Brynn Davies, for 16 years chairman of Mid Glamorgan Health Authority,
will not have his contract renewed this summer after a report highlighting
serious management failures.
The Commons committee on the parliamentary commissioner for administration
(the ombudsman) was told yesterday of his repeated failure to act on
complaints. The decision was made by Mr John Redwood, Welsh secretary.
Mr John Wyn Owen, a member of the National Health Service management
executive for Wales, told the committee action was being taken to improve
matters. In January Mr Davies apologised to the committee for the treatment
of the relatives of patients who tried for 18 months in vain to see a
consultant.
