FT  10 MAR 94 / Call for wider regulatory net
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The sale of savings products such as Tessas, which were seen as alternatives
to investment products, should be included in the retail financial services
regulatory regime, Mr Jim Stretton, deputy managing director of life insurer
Standard Life, said yesterday.
