FT  09 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Instem
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Improved performance and the completion of several large contracts during
the year helped Instem, the USM-quoted information systems group, lift
pre-tax profits for the year to December 31 to Pounds 1.02m.
This compares with Pounds 575,000 last time, when the figure was hit by an
exceptional Pounds 386,000 for bad debts.
Turnover was up from Pounds 14.3m to Pounds 19.3m and earnings per share
came out ahead at 14.8p (8.5p).
A same-again final of 1.8p is recommended, to give a total maintained at
3.1p.
