<HEADLINE>
FT  09 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Southern Newspapers surges to Pounds 7m
midway
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Profits at Southern Newspapers, the regional newspaper group, surged from
Pounds 3m to Pounds 7.15m pre-tax for the 26 weeks ended January 1. The
figure included a Pounds 3.5m profit from the sale of the group's
shareholding in Portsmouth &amp; Sunderland Newspapers.
Turnover improved to Pounds 36.62m (Pounds 35.41m), generating operating
profits of Pounds 3.58m (Pounds 2.95m). The group had noted a 'slight
improvement' in trading conditions since July.
The main contributor to the improved trading performance was the newspaper
division, although the magazine contract printing division increased
turnover by a 'significant' amount.
Earnings emerged at 25.28p (8.88p) and the interim dividend is being lifted
to 3.5p (3p).
The directors said the acquisitions of the Stour Valley News, Monitor
Business Magazine and the seven titles of the west country-based Star
Newspaper Group had yet to make a real impact on the results.
They added that the benefit of rationalisation programmes in all cases
should be seen in the second half.
The half year pre-tax result virtually matched the Pounds 7.51m returned for
the previous full year.
