<HEADLINE>
FT  09 MAR 94 / Observer: Altogether now
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Far from the European Union resulting in some boringly homogenised
bureaucratic idiom, it has actually thrown up some riveting divergences.
Thus British proposals about unemployment have been published with
translations adapted to local sensibilities. In the English text, Europe is
referred to as the (pre-Maastricht) European Community; the French version
calls it the (post-Maastricht) European Union. Thus are sensibilities
soothed.
</TEXT>
