<HEADLINE>
FT  09 MAR 94 / Observer: Crying wolf
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The idea that Martin Sorrell is about to sell off or float 'up to' 50 per
cent of the market research entities of his mammoth WPP advertising group
needs closer examination. Not to see if it's sensible; with debts of Pounds
361m it clearly is. But Sorrell has talked about doing it for the past two
years - since March 1992 - and little enough has happened so far. Having
worked so hard to build up WPP, Sorrell is not keen to see it fall apart. He
hates the thought of selling anything.
