<HEADLINE>
FT  09 MAR 94 / Hussein hopes to meet Fahd
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JAMES WHITTINGTON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   AMMAN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
King Hussein of Jordan led a delegation to Saudi Arabia yesterday, on his
first visit to the kingdom since relations deteriorated because of the
1990-1991 Gulf crisis, James Whittington writes from Amman.
Jordan's media reported the king had left for Saudi Arabia to perform the
Ummra, a minor Moslem pilgrimage. But officials acknowledged he was seeking
a meeting with King Fahd. One western diplomat in Amman described the trip
as 'significant'.
It demonstrated Jordan's desire to achieve a rapprochement with the Saudis,
still bitter over King Hussein's refusal to back the US-led effort to force
Iraq out of Kuwait in early 1991.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>SAZ  Saudi Arabia, Middle East.
</CN>
<XX>
