decide who should head their common list, or whether their Euro-MPs will sit
in the same political grouping at Strasbourg. Mr Valery Giscard d'Estaing's
UDF has been trying to persuade the RPR to join it in the Christian Democrat
grouping known as the European People's Party. Until now, the Gaullists have
sat together with Ireland's conservative Fianna Fail party in a separate
group, while deputies from the UDF have been split between the Liberal and
EPP groups.
